1. List all Docker images
docker images

or

docker image ls
2. Download an image from Docker Hub
docker pull image-name

Example:

docker pull ubuntu
3. Upload an image to Docker Hub
docker push image-name
4. Search for an image in Docker Hub
docker search image-name

Example:

docker search mysql
5. Delete an image from Docker Host
docker rmi image-name

Example:

docker rmi ubuntu
6. Create an image from a container
docker commit container-name/container-id image-name

Example:

docker commit mycontainer myimage
7. Create an image using a Dockerfile
docker build -t imagename .

Note:

. → represents the current working directory
2. Working with Docker Containers
8. List running containers
docker container ls
9. List all containers (running + stopped)
docker ps -a
10. Start a container
docker start container-name/container-id
11. Stop a container
docker stop container-name/container-id
12. Restart a container
docker restart container-name/container-id

Restart after 10 seconds

docker restart -t 10 container-name/container-id
13. Remove a stopped container
docker rm container-name/container-id
14. Remove a running container (force remove)
docker rm -f container-name/container-id
15. Stop all running containers
docker stop $(docker ps -aq)
16. Remove all stopped containers
docker rm $(docker ps -aq)
17. Remove all running containers
docker rm -f $(docker ps -aq)
18. View container logs
docker logs container-name/container-id
19. View container ports
docker port container-name/container-id
20. View detailed container information
docker inspect container-name/container-id
21. Create and run a container
docker run image-name

Example:

docker run ubuntu
3. Docker Networking Commands
22. List Docker networks
docker network ls
23. Inspect a network
docker network inspect network-id/network-name
24. Create a network
docker network create network-name
25. Delete a network
docker network rm network-id/network-name
